	   <tr><td colspan=2>Several dragons drop a light weight 100% weight reduction bag.&nbsp;&nbsp;USUALLY, because everyone knows about the weight restrictions placed on monks, the monks that are present get first shot at this bag IF they have a tinkerer's bag that they can trade for it if they win.  The lucky monk then surrenders a tinkerer's bag which is IDENTICAL to this except it is not lore and it weighs 1.0 instead of 0.4.  The rest of the raid members present then get to roll on the tinkerer's bag.  The only reason I can think of for someone to object to this is if they intended to sell the Treasure Hunter's Satchel.  In that case, the Satchel is definitely worth more than a Tinkerer's Bag.  A monk who got this item would NEVER sell it though.   <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
